## When to fan out
- **After** a code task whose verify PASSed, **before** the final report: run
  `code-reviewer` + `docs-drift-detector` in parallel on the working-tree diff.
- For wide, independent work (many files/subsystems): one agent per slice, in parallel.
- For verify-then-act loops: sequential, with a judge/verify step before committing.

## Rules
- Review the **diff** (`git add -N . && git diff`), never commit first to "have a diff".
- Fan out in ONE turn (multiple Agent calls) so they run concurrently.
- Fix blocker findings before finishing; list minor ones for the user.
- Skip fan-out for trivial/docs-only changes — and say so in the report.

## Anti-patterns
- Spawning agents for a one-line change.
- Re-deriving the architecture inside a sub-agent — it is already in `docs/`.
- Letting a sub-agent expand scope beyond the task.
